trailingComments.value:
*
* `XMLHttpRequest` wrapper with `Promise` logic.
*
* @example
* function on(event) {
*   console.info('on:', event.type, event);
* }
*
* new Request({
*   url   : 'http://192.168.1.102/command',
*   method: 'POST',
*   data  : 'version\n',
*   on    : {
*     'retry'            : on,
*     'retry.send'       : on,
*     'retry.limit'      : on,
*
*     'download.load'    : on,
*     'download.error'   : on,
*     'download.abort'   : on,
*     'download.timeout' : on,
*     'download.progress': on,
*
*     'upload.load'      : on,
*     'upload.error'     : on,
*     'upload.abort'     : on,
*     'upload.timeout'   : on,
*     'upload.progress'  : on
*   },
*   filters: {
*     status  : status => status === 200,
*     response: response => JSON.stringify(response)
*   }
* })
* .send()
* .then(event => {
*   console.info('then:', event);
* })
* .catch(event => {
*   console.error('catch:', event);
* });
*
* @see https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise
* @see https://pouchdb.com/2015/05/18/we-have-a-problem-with-promises.html
remove the first char if it is an '?'
